track_notes: Webb Peak Trail starts at Columbine Corrals campground.  There was a bad forest fire in 2017 which nearly erased the trail after the first quarter mile or so, but its not too difficult to continue up.
This was the track down.  See notes in Up track regarding fire damage to trail.

Short easy hike from trailhead to the summit. Almost a mile in length, 531 feet of gross elevation change and an average slope of 12 degrees. There is a fire watch tower at the summit and many trees from which to hang wire antennas.
track_title: Webb Peak from Trailhead to Summit

track_notes: Four years after the Frye Fire burned up most of the Webb Peak Trail, it is back along its original path. There is still some deadfall that you need to step over but the trail is mostly clear.  Its a great hike, although a VERY different feel than when I hiked it pre-fire.
